name: adexchangebuyer
title: Ad Exchange Buyer API
description: Accesses your bidding-account information, submits creatives for validation, finds available direct deals, and retrieves performance reports.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

fields.name: autoOptimizePrivateAuction
fields.desc: True if open auction buyers are allowed to compete with invited buyers in this private auction (buyer-readonly).

fields.name: reservePricePerBuyers
fields.desc: Reserve price for the specified buyer.

fields.name: dealIds
fields.desc: List of deals to delete for a given proposal

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The last known proposal revision number.

fields.name: updateAction
fields.desc: Indicates an optional action to take on the proposal

fields.name: companionSizes
fields.desc: For video size type, the list of companion sizes.

fields.name: creativeSizeType
fields.desc: The Creative size type.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: For regular or video creative size type, specifies the size of the creative.

fields.name: skippableAdType
fields.desc: The skippable ad type for video size.

schemas.name: AccountsList
schemas.desc: An account feed lists Ad Exchange buyer accounts that the user has access to. Each entry in the feed corresponds to a single buyer account.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: A list of accounts.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

schemas.name: Creative
schemas.desc: A creative and its classification data.

fields.name: agencyId
fields.desc: The agency id for this creative.

fields.name: attribute
fields.desc: List of buyer selectable attributes for the ads that may be shown from this snippet. Each attribute is represented by an integer as defined in  buyer-declarable-creative-attributes.txt.

fields.name: buyerCreativeId
fields.desc: A buyer-specific id identifying the creative in this ad.

fields.name: sensitiveCategories
fields.desc: Detected sensitive categories, if any. Each category is represented by an integer as defined in  ad-sensitive-categories.txt. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: clickThroughUrl
fields.desc: The set of destination urls for the snippet.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: Ad height.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Account id.

fields.name: filteringReasons
fields.desc: The filtering reasons for the creative. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: date
fields.desc: The date in ISO 8601 format for the data. The data is collected from 00:00:00 to 23:59:59 in PST.

fields.name: reasons
fields.desc: The filtering reasons.

fields.name: filteringCount
fields.desc: The number of times the creative was filtered for the status. The count is aggregated across all publishers on the exchange.

fields.name: filteringStatus
fields.desc: The filtering status code as defined in  creative-status-codes.txt.

fields.name: adChoicesDestinationUrl
fields.desc: The link to the Ad Preferences page. This is only supported for native ads.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: openAuctionStatus
fields.desc: Top-level open auction status. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests. If disapproved, an entry for auctionType=OPEN_AUCTION (or ALL) in servingRestrictions will also exist. Note that this may be nuanced with other contextual restrictions, in which case it may be preferable to read from ServingRestrictions directly.

fields.name: HTMLSnippet
fields.desc: The HTML snippet that displays the ad when inserted in the web page. If set, videoURL should not be set.

fields.name: nativeAd
fields.desc: If nativeAd is set, HTMLSnippet and the videoURL outside of nativeAd should not be set. (The videoURL inside nativeAd can be set.)

fields.name: starRating
fields.desc: The app rating in the app store. Must be in the range [0-5].

fields.name: videoURL
fields.desc: The URL of the XML VAST for a native ad. Note this is a separate field from resource.video_url.

fields.name: callToAction
fields.desc: A label for the button that the user is supposed to click.

fields.name: image
fields.desc: A large image.

fields.name: logo
fields.desc: A smaller image, for the advertiser logo.

fields.name: store
fields.desc: The URL to the app store to purchase/download the promoted app.

fields.name: appIcon
fields.desc: The app icon, for app download ads.

fields.name: body
fields.desc: A long description of the ad.

fields.name: clickTrackingUrl
fields.desc: The URL to use for click tracking.

fields.name: impressionTrackingUrl
fields.desc: The URLs are called when the impression is rendered.

fields.name: price
fields.desc: The price of the promoted app including the currency info.

fields.name: clickLinkUrl
fields.desc: The URL that the browser/SDK will load when the user clicks the ad.

fields.name: headline
fields.desc: A short title for the ad.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: Ad width.

fields.name: dealsStatus
fields.desc: Top-level deals status. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests. If disapproved, an entry for auctionType=DIRECT_DEALS (or ALL) in servingRestrictions will also exist. Note that this may be nuanced with other contextual restrictions, in which case it may be preferable to read from servingRestrictions directly.

fields.name: restrictedCategories
fields.desc: All restricted categories for the ads that may be shown from this snippet. Each category is represented by an integer as defined in the  ad-restricted-categories.txt.

fields.name: advertiserId
fields.desc: Detected advertiser id, if any. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: advertiserName
fields.desc: The name of the company being advertised in the creative. The value provided must exist in the advertisers.txt file.

fields.name: detectedDomains
fields.desc: Detected domains for this creative. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: impressionTrackingUrl
fields.desc: The set of urls to be called to record an impression.

fields.name: languages
fields.desc: Detected languages for this creative. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: productCategories
fields.desc: Detected product categories, if any. Each category is represented by an integer as defined in  ad-product-categories.txt. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: servingRestrictions
fields.desc: The granular status of this ad in specific contexts. A context here relates to where something ultimately serves (for example, a physical location, a platform, an HTTPS vs HTTP request, or the type of auction). Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: contexts
fields.desc: All known contexts/restrictions.

fields.name: auctionType
fields.desc: Only set when contextType=AUCTION_TYPE. Represents the auction types this restriction applies to.

fields.name: contextType
fields.desc: The type of context (e.g., location, platform, auction type, SSL-ness).

fields.name: geoCriteriaId
fields.desc: Only set when contextType=LOCATION. Represents the geo criterias this restriction applies to. Impressions are considered to match a context if either the user location or publisher location matches a given geoCriteriaId.

fields.name: platform
fields.desc: Only set when contextType=PLATFORM. Represents the platforms this restriction applies to.

fields.name: disapprovalReasons
fields.desc: The reasons for disapproval within this restriction, if any. Note that not all disapproval reasons may be categorized, so it is possible for the creative to have a status of DISAPPROVED or CONDITIONALLY_APPROVED with an empty list for disapproval_reasons. In this case, please reach out to your TAM to help debug the issue.

fields.name: details
fields.desc: Additional details about the reason for disapproval.

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: The categorized reason for disapproval.

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: Why the creative is ineligible to serve in this context (e.g., it has been explicitly disapproved or is pending review).

fields.name: version
fields.desc: The version for this creative. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: videoURL
fields.desc: The URL to fetch a video ad. If set, HTMLSnippet and the nativeAd should not be set. Note, this is different from resource.native_ad.video_url above.

fields.name: apiUploadTimestamp
fields.desc: The last upload timestamp of this creative if it was uploaded via API. Read-only. The value of this field is generated, and will be ignored for uploads. (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp).

fields.name: corrections
fields.desc: Shows any corrections that were applied to this creative. Read-only. This field should not be set in requests.

fields.name: contexts
fields.desc: All known serving contexts containing serving status information.

fields.name: auctionType
fields.desc: Only set when contextType=AUCTION_TYPE. Represents the auction types this correction applies to.

fields.name: contextType
fields.desc: The type of context (e.g., location, platform, auction type, SSL-ness).

fields.name: geoCriteriaId
fields.desc: Only set when contextType=LOCATION. Represents the geo criterias this correction applies to.

fields.name: platform
fields.desc: Only set when contextType=PLATFORM. Represents the platforms this correction applies to.

fields.name: details
fields.desc: Additional details about the correction.

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: The type of correction that was applied to the creative.

fields.name: vendorType
fields.desc: List of vendor types for the ads that may be shown from this snippet. Each vendor type is represented by an integer as defined in vendors.txt.

fields.name: fixedPrices
fields.desc: Fixed price for the specified buyer.

fields.name: guaranteedImpressions
fields.desc: Guaranteed impressions as a percentage. This is the percentage of guaranteed looks that the buyer is guaranteeing to buy.

fields.name: guaranteedLooks
fields.desc: Count of guaranteed looks. Required for deal, optional for product. For CPD deals, buyer changes to guaranteed_looks will be ignored.

fields.name: minimumDailyLooks
fields.desc: Count of minimum daily looks for a CPD deal. For CPD deals, buyer should negotiate on this field instead of guaranteed_looks.

fields.name: billingInfo
fields.desc: External billing info for this Deal. This field is relevant when external billing info such as price has a different currency code than DFP/AdX.

schemas.name: MarketplaceNote
schemas.desc: A proposal is associated with a bunch of notes which may optionally be associated with a deal and/or revision number.

fields.name: noteId
fields.desc: The unique id for the note. (readonly)

fields.name: proposalId
fields.desc: The proposalId that a note is attached to. (readonly)

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: If the note is associated with a proposal revision number, then store that here. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: timestampMs
fields.desc: The timestamp (ms since epoch) that this note was created. (readonly)

fields.name: creatorRole
fields.desc: The role of the person (buyer/seller) creating the note. (readonly)

fields.name: dealId
fields.desc: Notes can optionally be associated with a deal. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "adexchangebuyer#marketplaceNote".

fields.name: note
fields.desc: The actual note to attach. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: alcoholAdsAllowed
fields.desc: True if alcohol ads are allowed for this deal (read-only). This field is only populated when querying for finalized orders using the method GetFinalizedOrderDeals

fields.name: dealPauseStatus
fields.desc: Tracks which parties (if any) have paused a deal. (readonly, except via PauseResumeOrderDeals action)

fields.name: deals
fields.desc: List of deals to edit. Service may perform 3 different operations based on comparison of deals in this list vs deals already persisted in database: 1. Add new deal to proposal If a deal in this list does not exist in the proposal, the service will create a new deal and add it to the proposal. Validation will follow AddOrderDealsRequest. 2. Update existing deal in the proposal If a deal in this list already exist in the proposal, the service will update that existing deal to this new deal in the request. Validation will follow UpdateOrderDealsRequest. 3. Delete deals from the proposal (just need the id) If a existing deal in the proposal is not present in this list, the service will delete that deal from the proposal. Validation will follow DeleteOrderDealsRequest.

fields.name: proposal
fields.desc: If specified, also updates the proposal in the batch transaction. This is useful when the proposal and the deals need to be updated in one transaction.

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The last known revision number for the proposal.

fields.name: updateAction
fields.desc: Indicates an optional action to take on the proposal

fields.name: profileId
fields.desc: The pair of (seller.account_id, profile_id) uniquely identifies a publisher profile for a given publisher.

fields.name: programmaticContact
fields.desc: Programmatic contact for the publisher profile.

fields.name: publisherProvidedForecast
fields.desc: Publisher provided forecasting information.

fields.name: topHeadlines
fields.desc: Publisher provided key metrics and rankings.

fields.name: exchange
fields.desc: Exchange where this publisher profile is from. E.g. AdX, Rubicon etc...

fields.name: isParent
fields.desc: True, if this is the parent profile, which represents all domains owned by the publisher.

fields.name: logoUrl
fields.desc: The url to the logo for the publisher.

fields.name: samplePageLink
fields.desc: Link for a sample content page.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: State of the publisher profile.

fields.name: mediaKitLink
fields.desc: The url for additional marketing and sales materials.

fields.name: overview
fields.desc: Publisher provided overview.

fields.name: publisherProfileId
fields.desc: Unique Id for publisher profile.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "adexchangebuyer#publisherProfileApiProto".

fields.name: publisherDomains
fields.desc: The list of domains represented in this publisher profile. Empty if this is a parent profile.

fields.name: rateCardInfoLink
fields.desc: Link to publisher rate card

fields.name: buyerPitchStatement
fields.desc: A pitch statement for the buyer

fields.name: directContact
fields.desc: Direct contact for the publisher profile.

fields.name: googlePlusLink
fields.desc: Link to publisher's Google+ page.

fields.name: seller
fields.desc: Seller of the publisher profile.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: The account id of the seller.

fields.name: audience
fields.desc: Publisher provided info on its audience.

fields.name: isPublished
fields.desc: True, if this profile is published. Deprecated for state.

fields.name: exclusions
fields.desc: The list of values to exclude from targeting. Each value is AND'd together.

fields.name: inclusions
fields.desc: The list of value to include as part of the targeting. Each value is OR'd together.

fields.name: key
fields.desc: The key representing the shared targeting criterion.

schemas.name: BillingInfo
schemas.desc: The configuration data for an Ad Exchange billing info.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Account id.

fields.name: accountName
fields.desc: Account name.

fields.name: billingId
fields.desc: A list of adgroup IDs associated with this particular account. These IDs may show up as part of a realtime bidding BidRequest, which indicates a bid request for this account.

schemas.name: CreativesList
schemas.desc: The creatives feed lists the active creatives for the Ad Exchange buyer accounts that the user has access to. Each entry in the feed corresponds to a single creative.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: A list of creatives.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Continuation token used to page through creatives. To retrieve the next page of results, set the next request's "pageToken" value to this.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Id of the dimension.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Name of the dimension mainly for debugging purposes, except for the case of CREATIVE_SIZE. For CREATIVE_SIZE, strings are used instead of ids.

fields.name: percentage
fields.desc: Percent of total impressions for a dimension type. e.g. {dimension_type: 'GENDER', [{dimension_value: {id: 1, name: 'MALE', percentage: 60}}]} Gender MALE is 60% of all impressions which have gender.

fields.name: deals
fields.desc: List of deals deleted (in the same proposal as passed in the request)

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The updated revision number for the proposal.

schemas.name: PerformanceReportList
schemas.desc: The configuration data for an Ad Exchange performance report list.

fields.name: performanceReport
fields.desc: A list of performance reports relevant for the account.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

schemas.name: DealServingMetadataDealPauseStatus
schemas.desc: Tracks which parties (if any) have paused a deal. The deal is considered paused if has_buyer_paused || has_seller_paused. Each of the has_buyer_paused or the has_seller_paused bits can be set independently.

fields.name: firstPausedBy
fields.desc: If the deal is paused, records which party paused the deal first.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Description for the proposed terms of the deal.

fields.name: estimatedImpressionsPerDay
fields.desc: Non-binding estimate of the impressions served per day Can be set by buyer or seller.

fields.name: guaranteedFixedPriceTerms
fields.desc: The terms for guaranteed fixed price deals.

fields.name: nonGuaranteedAuctionTerms
fields.desc: The terms for non-guaranteed auction deals.

fields.name: nonGuaranteedFixedPriceTerms
fields.desc: The terms for non-guaranteed fixed price deals.

fields.name: brandingType
fields.desc: Visibilty of the URL in bid requests.

fields.name: crossListedExternalDealIdType
fields.desc: Indicates that this ExternalDealId exists under at least two different AdxInventoryDeals. Currently, the only case that the same ExternalDealId will exist is programmatic cross sell case.

fields.name: sellerTimeZone
fields.desc: For deals with Cost Per Day billing, defines the timezone used to mark the boundaries of a day (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: estimatedGrossSpend
fields.desc: Non-binding estimate of the estimated gross spend for this deal Can be set by buyer or seller.

fields.name: rubiconNonGuaranteedTerms
fields.desc: The terms for rubicon non-guaranteed deals.

schemas.name: PerformanceReport
schemas.desc: The configuration data for an Ad Exchange performance report list.

fields.name: hostedMatchStatusRate
fields.desc: Average QPS for hosted match operations.

fields.name: latency85thPercentile
fields.desc: The 85th percentile round trip latency(ms) as perceived from Google servers for the duration period covered by the report.

fields.name: outOfQuota
fields.desc: Rate of various quota account statuses per quota check.

fields.name: quotaConfiguredLimit
fields.desc: The configured quota limits for this account.

fields.name: cookieMatcherStatusRate
fields.desc: Average QPS for cookie matcher operations.

fields.name: filteredBidRate
fields.desc: The number of bid responses that were filtered due to a policy violation or other errors.

fields.name: latency95thPercentile
fields.desc: The 95th percentile round trip latency(ms) as perceived from Google servers for the duration period covered by the report.

fields.name: pixelMatchRequests
fields.desc: Average QPS for pixel match requests from clients.

fields.name: region
fields.desc: The trading location of this data.

fields.name: bidRequestRate
fields.desc: The number of bid requests sent to your bidder.

fields.name: creativeStatusRate
fields.desc: Rate of ads with a given status. Please refer to the creative-status-codes.txt file for different statuses.

fields.name: inventoryMatchRate
fields.desc: The number of potential queries based on your pretargeting settings.

fields.name: noQuotaInRegion
fields.desc: Rate of various quota account statuses per quota check.

fields.name: pixelMatchResponses
fields.desc: Average QPS for pixel match responses from clients.

fields.name: quotaThrottledLimit
fields.desc: The throttled quota limits for this account.

fields.name: successfulRequestRate
fields.desc: The number of properly formed bid responses received by our servers within the deadline.

fields.name: timestamp
fields.desc: The unix timestamp of the starting time of this performance data.

fields.name: bidRate
fields.desc: The number of bid responses with an ad.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: latency50thPercentile
fields.desc: The 50th percentile round trip latency(ms) as perceived from Google servers for the duration period covered by the report.

fields.name: unsuccessfulRequestRate
fields.desc: The number of bid responses that were unsuccessful due to timeouts, incorrect formatting, etc.

fields.name: calloutStatusRate
fields.desc: Rate of various prefiltering statuses per match. Please refer to the callout-status-codes.txt file for different statuses.

schemas.name: BillingInfoList
schemas.desc: A billing info feed lists Billing Info the Ad Exchange buyer account has access to. Each entry in the feed corresponds to a single billing info.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: A list of billing info relevant for your account.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

schemas.name: Proposal
schemas.desc:
Represents a proposal in the marketplace. A proposal is the unit of negotiation between a seller and a buyer and contains deals which are served. Each field in a proposal can have one of the following setting:

(readonly) - It is an error to try and set this field. (buyer-readonly) - Only the seller can set this field. (seller-readonly) - Only the buyer can set this field. (updatable) - The field is updatable at all times by either buyer or the seller.

fields.name: hasBuyerSignedOff
fields.desc: When an proposal is in an accepted state, indicates whether the buyer has signed off. Once both sides have signed off on a deal, the proposal can be finalized by the seller. (seller-readonly)

fields.name: buyerContacts
fields.desc: Optional contact information of the buyer. (seller-readonly)

fields.name: dbmAdvertiserIds
fields.desc: IDs of DBM advertisers permission to this proposal.

fields.name: isRenegotiating
fields.desc: True if the proposal is being renegotiated (readonly).

fields.name: originatorRole
fields.desc: Indicates whether the buyer/seller created the proposal.(readonly)

fields.name: proposalState
fields.desc: The current state of the proposal. (readonly)

fields.name: seller
fields.desc: Reference to the seller on the proposal. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: buyer
fields.desc: Reference to the buyer on the proposal. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: buyerPrivateData
fields.desc: Private data for buyer. (hidden from seller).

fields.name: inventorySource
fields.desc: What exchange will provide this inventory (readonly, except on create).

fields.name: isSetupComplete
fields.desc: True, if the buyside inventory setup is complete for this proposal. (readonly, except via OrderSetupCompleted action)

fields.name: proposalId
fields.desc: The unique id of the proposal. (readonly).

fields.name: revisionNumber
fields.desc: The revision number for the proposal (readonly).

fields.name: sellerContacts
fields.desc: Optional contact information of the seller (buyer-readonly).

fields.name: privateAuctionId
fields.desc: Optional private auction id if this proposal is a private auction proposal.

fields.name: billedBuyer
fields.desc: Reference to the buyer that will get billed for this proposal. (readonly)

fields.name: hasSellerSignedOff
fields.desc: When an proposal is in an accepted state, indicates whether the buyer has signed off Once both sides have signed off on a deal, the proposal can be finalized by the seller. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "adexchangebuyer#proposal".

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: List of labels associated with the proposal. (readonly)

fields.name: lastUpdaterOrCommentorRole
fields.desc: The role of the last user that either updated the proposal or left a comment. (readonly)

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name for the proposal (updatable)

fields.name: negotiationId
fields.desc: Optional negotiation id if this proposal is a preferred deal proposal.

fields.name: revisionTimeMs
fields.desc: The time (ms since epoch) when the proposal was last revised (readonly).

fields.name: notes
fields.desc: The list of matching notes. The notes for a proposal are ordered from oldest to newest. If the notes span multiple proposals, they will be grouped by proposal, with the notes for the most recently modified proposal appearing first.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: A list of pretargeting configs

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: proposals
fields.desc: The list of proposals successfully created.

fields.name: deals
fields.desc: List of all deals in the proposal after edit.

fields.name: orderRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The latest revision number after the update has been applied.

fields.name: dfpLineItemId
fields.desc: The DFP line item id associated with this deal. For features like CPD, buyers can retrieve the DFP line item for billing reconciliation.

fields.name: originalContractedQuantity
fields.desc: The original contracted quantity (# impressions) for this deal. To ensure delivery, sometimes the publisher will book the deal with a impression buffer, such that guaranteed_looks is greater than the contracted quantity. However clients are billed using the original contracted quantity.

fields.name: price
fields.desc: The original reservation price for the deal, if the currency code is different from the one used in negotiation.

fields.name: currencyConversionTimeMs
fields.desc: The timestamp (in ms since epoch) when the original reservation price for the deal was first converted to DFP currency. This is used to convert the contracted price into advertiser's currency without discrepancy.

fields.name: products
fields.desc: The returned list of products.

fields.name: notes
fields.desc: The list of notes to add.

fields.name: email
fields.desc: Email address of the contact.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the contact.

fields.name: proposals
fields.desc: The list of proposals to create.

fields.name: webPropertyCode
fields.desc: Web property id of the seller creating these orders

fields.name: amountMicros
fields.desc: The price value in micros.

fields.name: currencyCode
fields.desc: The currency code for the price.

fields.name: expectedCpmMicros
fields.desc: In case of CPD deals, the expected CPM in micros.

fields.name: pricingType
fields.desc: The pricing type for the deal/product.

fields.name: externalDealId
fields.desc: The externalDealId of the deal to be updated.

fields.name: note
fields.desc: Optional note to be added.

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The current revision number of the proposal to be updated.

fields.name: updateAction
fields.desc: The proposed action on the private auction proposal.

schemas.name: Account
schemas.desc: Configuration data for an Ad Exchange buyer account.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: maximumActiveCreatives
fields.desc: The maximum number of active creatives that an account can have, where a creative is active if it was inserted or bid with in the last 30 days. Please contact your technical account manager if you need to change this.

fields.name: maximumTotalQps
fields.desc: The sum of all bidderLocation.maximumQps values cannot exceed this. Please contact your technical account manager if you need to change this.

fields.name: numberActiveCreatives
fields.desc: The number of creatives that this account inserted or bid with in the last 30 days.

fields.name: bidderLocation
fields.desc: Your bidder locations that have distinct URLs.

fields.name: bidProtocol
fields.desc:
The protocol that the bidder endpoint is using. OpenRTB protocols with prefix PROTOCOL_OPENRTB_PROTOBUF use proto buffer, otherwise use JSON.  Allowed values:  
- PROTOCOL_ADX 
- PROTOCOL_OPENRTB_2_2 
- PROTOCOL_OPENRTB_2_3 
- PROTOCOL_OPENRTB_2_4 
- PROTOCOL_OPENRTB_PROTOBUF_2_3 
- PROTOCOL_OPENRTB_PROTOBUF_2_4

fields.name: maximumQps
fields.desc: The maximum queries per second the Ad Exchange will send.

fields.name: region
fields.desc:
The geographical region the Ad Exchange should send requests from. Only used by some quota systems, but always setting the value is recommended. Allowed values:  
- ASIA 
- EUROPE 
- US_EAST 
- US_WEST

fields.name: url
fields.desc: The URL to which the Ad Exchange will send bid requests.

fields.name: cookieMatchingNid
fields.desc: The nid parameter value used in cookie match requests. Please contact your technical account manager if you need to change this.

fields.name: cookieMatchingUrl
fields.desc: The base URL used in cookie match requests.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Account id.

fields.name: deals
fields.desc: List of deals for the proposal

fields.name: label
fields.desc: The label to use.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: The accountId of the party that created the label.

fields.name: createTimeMs
fields.desc: The creation time (in ms since epoch) for the label.

fields.name: deprecatedMarketplaceDealParty
fields.desc: Information about the party that created the label.

fields.name: fixedPrices
fields.desc: Fixed price for the specified buyer.

schemas.name: Product
schemas.desc:
A product is segment of inventory that a seller wishes to sell. It is associated with certain terms and targeting information which helps buyer know more about the inventory. Each field in a product can have one of the following setting:

(readonly) - It is an error to try and set this field. (buyer-readonly) - Only the seller can set this field. (seller-readonly) - Only the buyer can set this field. (updatable) - The field is updatable at all times by either buyer or the seller.

fields.name: inventorySource
fields.desc: What exchange will provide this inventory (readonly, except on create).

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: Optional List of labels for the product (optional, buyer-readonly).

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name for this product as set by the seller. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: publisherProfileId
fields.desc: Id of the publisher profile for a given seller. A (seller.account_id, publisher_profile_id) pair uniquely identifies a publisher profile. Buyers can call the PublisherProfiles::List endpoint to get a list of publisher profiles for a given seller.

fields.name: syndicationProduct
fields.desc: The syndication product associated with the deal. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "adexchangebuyer#product".

fields.name: privateAuctionId
fields.desc: Optional private auction id if this offer is a private auction offer.

fields.name: productId
fields.desc: The unique id for the product (readonly)

fields.name: state
fields.desc: The state of the product. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: terms
fields.desc: The negotiable terms of the deal (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: webPropertyCode
fields.desc: The web property code for the seller. This field is meant to be copied over as is when creating deals.

fields.name: creatorContacts
fields.desc: Optional contact information for the creator of this product. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: deliveryControl
fields.desc: The set of fields around delivery control that are interesting for a buyer to see but are non-negotiable. These are set by the publisher. This message is assigned an id of 100 since some day we would want to model this as a protobuf extension.

fields.name: flightEndTimeMs
fields.desc: The proposed end time for the deal (ms since epoch) (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: legacyOfferId
fields.desc: Optional legacy offer id if this offer is a preferred deal offer.

fields.name: publisherProvidedForecast
fields.desc: Publisher self-provided forecast information.

fields.name: revisionNumber
fields.desc: The revision number of the product. (readonly)

fields.name: sharedTargetings
fields.desc: Targeting that is shared between the buyer and the seller. Each targeting criteria has a specified key and for each key there is a list of inclusion value or exclusion values. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: creationTimeMs
fields.desc: Creation time in ms. since epoch (readonly)

fields.name: flightStartTimeMs
fields.desc: Inventory availability dates. (times are in ms since epoch) The granularity is generally in the order of seconds. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: hasCreatorSignedOff
fields.desc: If the creator has already signed off on the product, then the buyer can finalize the deal by accepting the product as is. When copying to a proposal, if any of the terms are changed, then auto_finalize is automatically set to false.

fields.name: lastUpdateTimeMs
fields.desc: Time of last update in ms. since epoch (readonly)

fields.name: marketplacePublisherProfileId
fields.desc: Marketplace publisher profile Id. This Id differs from the regular publisher_profile_id in that 1. This is a new id, the old Id will be deprecated in 2017. 2. This id uniquely identifies a publisher profile by itself.

fields.name: seller
fields.desc: Information about the seller that created this product (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: The unique id for the seller. The seller fills in this field. The seller account id is then available to buyer in the product.

fields.name: subAccountId
fields.desc: Optional sub-account id for the seller.

fields.name: stringValue
fields.desc: The string value to exclude/include.

fields.name: creativeSizeValue
fields.desc: The creative size value to exclude/include.

fields.name: dayPartTargetingValue
fields.desc: The daypart targeting to include / exclude. Filled in when the key is GOOG_DAYPART_TARGETING.

fields.name: longValue
fields.desc: The long value to exclude/include.

fields.name: deals
fields.desc: List of deals added (in the same proposal as passed in the request)

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The updated revision number for the proposal.

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: Adx account id of the buyer.

schemas.name: PublisherProvidedForecast
schemas.desc: This message carries publisher provided forecasting information.

fields.name: weeklyImpressions
fields.desc: Publisher provided weekly impressions.

fields.name: weeklyUniques
fields.desc: Publisher provided weekly uniques.

fields.name: dimensions
fields.desc: Publisher provided dimensions. E.g. geo, sizes etc...

fields.name: buyer
fields.desc: The buyer/seller associated with the deal. One of buyer/seller is specified for a deal-party.

fields.name: seller
fields.desc: The buyer/seller associated with the deal. One of buyer/seller is specified for a deal party.

fields.name: excludedUserLists
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these users list ids will not match.

fields.name: excludedVerticals
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these vertical ids will not match. Values are from the publisher-verticals.txt file in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: userLists
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these user list ids will match.

fields.name: vendorTypes
fields.desc: Requests that allow any of these vendor ids will match. Values are from vendors.txt in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: configId
fields.desc: The config id; generated automatically. Leave this field blank for insert requests.

fields.name: creativeType
fields.desc: List must contain exactly one of PRETARGETING_CREATIVE_TYPE_HTML or PRETARGETING_CREATIVE_TYPE_VIDEO.

fields.name: excludedGeoCriteriaIds
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these geo criteria ids will not match.

fields.name: geoCriteriaIds
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these geo criteria ids will match.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of the resource, i.e. "adexchangebuyer#pretargetingConfig".

fields.name: minimumViewabilityDecile
fields.desc: Requests where the predicted viewability is below the specified decile will not match. E.g. if the buyer sets this value to 5, requests from slots where the predicted viewability is below 50% will not match. If the predicted viewability is unknown this field will be ignored.

fields.name: mobileCarriers
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these mobile carrier ids will match. Values are from mobile-carriers.csv in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: placements
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these placements will match.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: The value of the placement. Interpretation depends on the placement type, e.g. URL for a site placement, channel name for a channel placement, app id for a mobile app placement.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the placement.

fields.name: billingId
fields.desc: The id for billing purposes, provided for reference. Leave this field blank for insert requests; the id will be generated automatically.

fields.name: platforms
fields.desc: Requests matching any of these platforms will match. Possible values are PRETARGETING_PLATFORM_MOBILE, PRETARGETING_PLATFORM_DESKTOP, and PRETARGETING_PLATFORM_TABLET.

fields.name: dimensions
fields.desc: Requests which allow one of these (width, height) pairs will match. All pairs must be supported ad dimensions.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: Height in pixels.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: Width in pixels.

fields.name: excludedPlacements
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these placements will not match.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: The value of the placement. Interpretation depends on the placement type, e.g. URL for a site placement, channel name for a channel placement, app id for a mobile app placement.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the placement.

fields.name: isActive
fields.desc: Whether this config is active. Required for all requests.

fields.name: languages
fields.desc: Request containing any of these language codes will match.

fields.name: mobileDevices
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these mobile device ids will match. Values are from mobile-devices.csv in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: verticals
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these vertical ids will match.

fields.name: configName
fields.desc: The name of the config. Must be unique. Required for all requests.

fields.name: mobileOperatingSystemVersions
fields.desc: Requests containing any of these mobile operating system version ids will match. Values are from mobile-os.csv in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: supportedCreativeAttributes
fields.desc: Creative attributes should be declared here if all creatives corresponding to this pretargeting configuration have that creative attribute. Values are from pretargetable-creative-attributes.txt in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: userIdentifierDataRequired
fields.desc: Requests containing the specified type of user data will match. Possible values are HOSTED_MATCH_DATA, which means the request is cookie-targetable and has a match in the buyer's hosted match table, and COOKIE_OR_IDFA, which means the request has either a targetable cookie or an iOS IDFA.

fields.name: videoPlayerSizes
fields.desc: Video requests satisfying any of these player size constraints will match.

fields.name: aspectRatio
fields.desc: The type of aspect ratio. Leave this field blank to match all aspect ratios.

fields.name: minHeight
fields.desc: The minimum player height in pixels. Leave this field blank to match any player height.

fields.name: minWidth
fields.desc: The minimum player width in pixels. Leave this field blank to match any player width.

fields.name: excludedContentLabels
fields.desc: Requests with any of these content labels will not match. Values are from content-labels.txt in the downloadable files section.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: The height of the creative.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: The width of the creative.

fields.name: standardPrice
fields.desc: Optional price for Rubicon standard access in the auction.

fields.name: priorityPrice
fields.desc: Optional price for Rubicon priority access in the auction.

schemas.name: MarketplaceDeal
schemas.desc: A proposal can contain multiple deals. A deal contains the terms and targeting information that is used for serving.

fields.name: sharedTargetings
fields.desc: The shared targeting visible to buyers and sellers. Each shared targeting entity is AND'd together. (updatable)

fields.name: terms
fields.desc: The negotiable terms of the deal. (updatable)

fields.name: externalDealId
fields.desc: The external deal id assigned to this deal once the deal is finalized. This is the deal-id that shows up in serving/reporting etc. (readonly)

fields.name: flightEndTimeMs
fields.desc: Proposed flight end time of the deal (ms since epoch) This will generally be stored in a granularity of a second. (updatable)

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "adexchangebuyer#marketplaceDeal".

fields.name: programmaticCreativeSource
fields.desc: Specifies the creative source for programmatic deals, PUBLISHER means creative is provided by seller and ADVERTISR means creative is provided by buyer. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: lastUpdateTimeMs
fields.desc: The time (ms since epoch) when the deal was last updated. (readonly)

fields.name: creativePreApprovalPolicy
fields.desc: Specifies the creative pre-approval policy (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: flightStartTimeMs
fields.desc: Proposed flight start time of the deal (ms since epoch) This will generally be stored in a granularity of a second. (updatable)

fields.name: inventoryDescription
fields.desc: Description for the deal terms. (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: isRfpTemplate
fields.desc: Indicates whether the current deal is a RFP template. RFP template is created by buyer and not based on seller created products.

fields.name: creationTimeMs
fields.desc: The time (ms since epoch) of the deal creation. (readonly)

fields.name: dealServingMetadata
fields.desc: Metadata about the serving status of this deal (readonly, writes via custom actions)

fields.name: productId
fields.desc: The product-id from which this deal was created. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: sellerContacts
fields.desc: Optional Seller contact information for the deal (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the deal. (updatable)

fields.name: productRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The revision number of the product that the deal was created from (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: syndicationProduct
fields.desc: The syndication product associated with the deal. (readonly, except on create)

fields.name: buyerPrivateData
fields.desc: Buyer private data (hidden from seller).

fields.name: creativeSafeFrameCompatibility
fields.desc: Specifies whether the creative is safeFrame compatible (buyer-readonly)

fields.name: dealId
fields.desc: A unique deal-id for the deal (readonly).

fields.name: deliveryControl
fields.desc: The set of fields around delivery control that are interesting for a buyer to see but are non-negotiable. These are set by the publisher. This message is assigned an id of 100 since some day we would want to model this as a protobuf extension.

schemas.name: Dimension
schemas.desc: This message carries publisher provided breakdown. E.g. {dimension_type: 'COUNTRY', [{dimension_value: {id: 1, name: 'US'}}, {dimension_value: {id: 2, name: 'UK'}}]}

fields.name: proposals
fields.desc: The list of matching proposals.

fields.name: updateAction
fields.desc: Indicates an optional action to take on the proposal

fields.name: deals
fields.desc: The list of deals to add

fields.name: proposalRevisionNumber
fields.desc: The last known proposal revision number.

schemas.name: Budget
schemas.desc: The configuration data for Ad Exchange RTB - Budget API.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The unique id that describes this item.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of the resource, i.e. "adexchangebuyer#budget".

fields.name: accountId
fields.desc: The id of the account. This is required for get and update requests.

fields.name: billingId
fields.desc: The billing id to determine which adgroup to provide budget information for. This is required for get and update requests.

fields.name: budgetAmount
fields.desc: The daily budget amount in unit amount of the account currency to apply for the billingId provided. This is required for update requests.

fields.name: currencyCode
fields.desc: The currency code for the buyer. This cannot be altered here.

schemas.name: CreativeDealIds
schemas.desc: The external deal ids associated with a creative.

fields.name: dealStatuses
fields.desc: A list of external deal ids and ARC approval status.

fields.name: arcStatus
fields.desc: ARC approval status.

fields.name: dealId
fields.desc: External deal ID.

fields.name: webPropertyId
fields.desc: Publisher ID.

fields.desc: Resource type.

fields.name: profiles
fields.desc: Profiles for the requested publisher

schemas.name: PricePerBuyer
schemas.desc: Used to specify pricing rules for buyers/advertisers. Each PricePerBuyer in an product can become [0,1] deals. To check if there is a PricePerBuyer for a particular buyer or buyer/advertiser pair, we look for the most specific matching rule - we first look for a rule matching the buyer and advertiser, next a rule with the buyer but an empty advertiser list, and otherwise look for a matching rule where no buyer is set.

fields.name: auctionTier
fields.desc: Optional access type for this buyer.

fields.name: buyer
fields.desc: The buyer who will pay this price. If unset, all buyers can pay this price (if the advertisers match, and there's no more specific rule matching the buyer).

fields.name: price
fields.desc: The specified price
